===Etymology===
From Mandarin Chinese [[閩]][[南]] / [[闽]][[南]] (Mǐn Nán), "Southern [[Min]]".

===Noun===

# '''Mǐn Nán''' ([[Simplified Chinese]]: 闽南语, [[Traditional Chinese]]: 閩南語), also spelt as '''Minnan''' or '''Min-nan''' in English; native name '''[[Bân-lâm-gú]]'''. It refers to the local language/dialect of southern [[Fujian]] province, [[China]]. It is often known simply as [[Hokkien]] or [[Teochew]], especially in [[Southeast Asia]]. It belongs to the Eastern [[Min]] dialect group of the [[Sinitic]] branch of the [[Sino-Tibetan]] language family. There are 49 million speakers of Min Nan in [[China]], [[Singapore]], [[Indonesia]], [[Malaysia]], [[Taiwan]], and other areas of the world.

